Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16555&quot; title=&quot;print more YAML compatible special chars for jobid&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16555&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16555&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; obdclass: quote jobid with &apos;:&apos; char&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 27729ac227266699730b5c39dfdad4c5533f88a5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="364305" author="adilger" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2023 01:44:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, if &quot;:&quot;  is at the end then the JobID needs to be quoted or there is a YAML parsing error.  When I reviewed the original 49998 patch I thought this couldn&apos;t happen easily, but with the empty &quot;&lt;tt&gt;jobid_var&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; variable and a &quot;:&quot; separator this is easy to hit (or even if users just add a &quot;:&quot; at the end of &lt;tt&gt;jobid_name&lt;/tt&gt; for whatever reason).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="364304" author="flei" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2023 00:50:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we need 3 types of chars:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;common chars (alnum +&quot;.@-_:/&quot;), which can be printed literally&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;other chars which should be escaped&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;chars which indicate jobid should be quoted, which is actually chars of 2 + &apos;:&apos;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Make sense?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="364247" author="adilger" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2023 17:19:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just saw a system with JobIDs that look like &quot;0:0:&quot; or  &quot;12345:23456:&quot;, which is apparently &quot;%u:%g:%j&quot;, where &quot;%j&quot; is unset on login nodes.   This is causing YAML parsing by collecd to fail in the case where &quot;:&quot; is at the end of the JobID string.  Pasting these job_stats into &lt;a href=&quot;http://yaml-online-parser.appspot.com/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://yaml-online-parser.appspot.com/&lt;/a&gt; confirms that quoting the &quot;0:0:&quot; string fixes the parsing error. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="363875" author="pjones" created="Thu, 23 Feb 2023 14:03:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.16&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
